						               													<description>&amp;quot;But, Colonel! You're asking us to attack other US citizens!&amp;quot; &amp;quot;Do your work, soldier! This is Divided America.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Divided America: The Next Civil War is a simulation game of a hypothetical near-future conflict within the once United States. A presidential election has just concluded, and no clear winner has arisen. Martial law is declared, but competing factions on the Joint Chiefs of Staff result in a divided military, and militia forces are popping up in the urban centers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is YOUR chance to command one of those military forces, or a militia force, and see if you can overcome your enemies and restore some measure of control over Divided America.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Designed in the classic hex-and-counter style of &amp;quot;military chess&amp;quot; game playing popularized in the 1970s and 1980s, this game lets you decide the fate of the republic.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Battles take place on a brand new  original map which has a simplified terrain representation of the lower-48 states. Cities, forests, rivers, lakes, and coasts are among the terrain types represented on the map.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In a civil war, will militia units do well, or run away? Will military units fire on civilians, even if they have taken up arms? What will happen in a Divided America? And over it all hovers the fear of who has the `nuclear football'? Will nuclear attacks happen?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game Facts: Three sets of double-sided counters made by professional artists, an original map commissioned just for this game, and a comprehensive 60 page rules book.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1-3 players ages 10+ with great solo rules. Game length 45 minutes to several hours Numerous and varied scenarios, from a quick skirmish to the huge country wide game 'when the SHTF'&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
